ENTRY            30470   20260425   20260508   20260508       3222
SUBENT        30470001   20260425   20260508   20260508       3222
BIB                 12         37
TITLE      Inelastic scattering of 14.8 MeV neutrons from deuteron
AUTHOR     (K.Gul, A.Waheed, M.Ahmed, M.Saleem, N.A.Khan)
INSTITUTE  (3PAKNIL)
REFERENCE  (J,JP/G,5,1107,1979)
           (R,PINST-NPD-4,197808)
           Int.rep.NPD-4(FNFG),preliminary.
FACILITY   (CCW,3PAKNIL) Pinstech neutron generator facility
INC-SOURCE (D-T)
DETECTOR   (SCIN) NE-213 scintillator, 2 inch X 2 inch, placed in
            a borated wax and lead shielding.
           . NE-230 scintillator as scatterer provided a stop
            signal for the time-to-pulse amplitude converter.
           . Neutron-gamma pulse shape discrimination was applied.
METHOD     (TOF,ASSOP) The scatterer(NE-230) was placed at about
           12 cm from the neutron target.
MONITOR    No standard used. Neutron flux was determined by
            associated particle method. The absolute efficiency
            of the neutron detector was experimentally determined
            from its response to the known flux of monoenergetic
            neutrons.(See Waheed et al.,Pinstech Int.Rep.No.5(NPD)
            (FNPG).  Then the measured efficiency was fitted to
            the value obtained with Monte Carlo calculation.
           The side experiment of carbon breakup was used to
            verify the efficiency curve.
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-T) An over all error of 10% includes:
           (ERR-S) background statistics about (7%)
           (ERR-1) the number of deuterons in the scatterer (2%)
           (ERR-2) the efficiency of the neutron detector (7%)
           (ERR-3) multiple scattering correction (1%)
STATUS     (APRVD) Approved by K.Gul with amendment,79/05/14.
HISTORY    (19790317R) Data received from K.Gul as private
            communication (1979-03-17)
           (19790406C) KO.
           (19790619A) KO.-'Aprvd' added. Correct. after preprint-
           (19800118U) KO. -Minor correction in subent .003.
           (20090310A) SD: Updated to new date formats, lower case
           (20260325A) VT. Revision in 002-005
ENDBIB              37
