SUBENT        30470004   20260425   20260508   20260508       3222
BIB                  5         17
REACTION   (1-H-2(N,2N)1-H-1,,SIG,,,DERIV)
            Deuteron break-up cross-section.
ANALYSIS   Assuming a constant value for cross-section beyond 75
            degree, the neutron emission cross-section in forward
            hemisphere was obtained to be
           . 240+/-30 mb, this gives
           . 120+/-15 mb for proton emission(=deuteron
            break-up) cross-sections in forward hemisphere.
           The value of proton emission in the backward-
            direction (=25 mb) by N.Koori was added.
ASSUMED    Proton emission in the backward direction equal to
            25 mb by N.Koori,J.Phys.Soc.Japan,32(1972)306
